parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Fuel Filler Pipe and Surrounding Components
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the fuel filler pipe and surrounding components can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, and result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: excessive corrosion of the fuel filler pipe and surrounding mounts
failure of the stamped metal bowl surrounding the filler pipe
excessive fumes building up within the car

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine's inability to idle properly and maintain power can cause stalling, loss of power, and overheating, which can lead to accidents, stranded drivers, and engine damage.
symptoms: Engine idles poorly when warm or cold
loss of power on the freeway
engine overheating after long driving stints
fan failure to engage when engine is overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty oxygen sensors can cause poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions, which can lead to higher fuel costs and environmental harm.
symptoms: Vehicle not achieving maximum gas mileage per gallon
oxygen sensor replacement required multiple times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Insufficient seat belt length can prevent proper fastening, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The front seat belts are not long enough to fasten when the seats are in the forward position
making it difficult or impossible to securely fasten the seat belt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to lock up, preventing proper fastening and increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The rear drive side retractor locks up
preventing the seat belt from functioning properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning seat belt fastener can prevent the seat belt from engaging properly, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The metal fastener does not engage into the seat belt locking mechanism properly
making it difficult or impossible to securely fasten the seat belt.
